OL,3,CFraudster jailed for duping luxury
OL,4,Chotels into buying his fake Scottish
OL,5,Ctea
OL,7,FThomas Robinson, 55, who also went by
OL,8,FThomas O'Brien or Tam O'Braan, was
OL,9,Ffound guilt of deceiving luxury stores
OL,10,Fand hotel groups into buying his
OL,11,F'unique' Scottish-grown tea that was
OL,12,Fin fact wholesale leaves he had
OL,13,Fimported from around the world and
OL,14,Frepackaged.
OL,16,FHis victims included five-star hotels
OL,17,Flike London's Dorchester and
OL,18,FEdinburgh's Balmoral which are known
OL,19,Ffor their grand afternoon tea
OL,20,Fexperiences.
